      "end": 4.7,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.48,
      "end": 11.26,
      "text": "For more information and to find out how to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.2,
      "end": 16.04,
      "text": "Recorded by Marion Brown, Toronto, Canada.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.34,
      "end": 20.64,
      "text": "ESOP's Fables, the Ass in the Lion Skin.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.92,
      "end": 28.86,
      "text": "The Ass in the Lion Skin. An Ass found a lion skin and dressed himself up in it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.86,
      "end": 36.34,
      "text": "Then he went about frightening everyone he met. For they all took him to be a lion, men and beasts alike,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 37.1,
      "end": 44.54,
      "text": "and took to their heels when they saw him coming. Elated by the success of his trick, he loudly braid in triumph.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 45.38,
      "end": 50.42,
      "text": "The Fox heard him and recognized him at once for the Ass he was, and said to him,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 50.84,
      "end": 56.4,
      "text": "Ho Ho my friend, it's you, is it? I too should have been afraid if I hadn't heard your voice.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 57.76,
      "end": 60.78,
      "text": "ESOP's Fables, the Ass in the Lion Skin.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
